In a job step, import the adaptor and chain its operations. Each operation reads and writes to job state, so the response from one becomes the input to the next:

import { createCustomer, initiatePayment, createPaymentMethod } from "@openfn/language-flutterwave";

createCustomer({ /* params */ });

The Snippets tab has 5 ready-to-paste examples grouped by category — start there rather than from scratch.
